<div class="quotetitle">djcouchycouch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Any suggestions for a tool that: <br /><br />- takes a bitmap <br />- breaks it into 8x8 tiles <br />- removes duplicates<br />- saves the tiles into a separate bitmap <br />- creates array of tile indexes to rebuild the bitmap as tiles<br />- saves array to a file<br /></div><br /><br />This is easily done with <a href="http://www.coranac.com/projects/grit/" class="postlink">grit</a>: <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">grit input.png -m -fx tiles.png</tt>. See <a href="http://www.coranac.com/man/grit/html/grit.htm" class="postlink">the manual</a> for details.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5656">dasi</a> — Sat Dec 08, 2012 7:27 pm</p><hr />
