<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Tool that breaks up bitmap, removes duplicate tiles, etc]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9586&amp;p=104275#p104275"><![CDATA[
<a href="http://pyxeledit.com/" class="postlink">Pyxel Edit</a><br />It can do everything in your list. (though the way it saves an array to a file may not be best for you. But whatever)<br />Import an image with 8x8 tile size. It will check for duplicates, even transformations. (Sadly you can't choose which transformations. For instance, You want it to check for X and Y flipped tiles but not rotations.)<br /><br />It's a pretty self explanatory program.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3504">Kasumi</a> — Fri Dec 07, 2012 10:13 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
